[This is now the 3rd consecutive day with no new cases reported -- 25 more days of no new cases until transmission of MERS-CoV will be considered interrupted. Unfortunately there was a newly reported fatality. There have been a total of 182 cases including 33 fatalities for a reported case fatality rate of 18.1 percent. There remain 13 individuals in critical condition. Overall there have been 13 354 individuals released from quarantine with a residual 2638 still under quarantine (duration of quarantine has been defined as 14 days following most recent date of exposure to a known laboratory confirmed case).

The HealthMap/ProMED map of South Korea can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3472461,195. - Mod.MPP]

