As of 12 Noon today, 29 Jun 2015 there have been a total of:
1041 laboratory confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection including
460 deaths
577 recoveries, and
4 currently active cases

In the past 24 hours there has been
1 newly confirmed case
0 newly reported deaths
0 newly reported recoveries

[the reported case fatality rate is 44.2 percent]

Information on newly confirmed case today, 29 Jun 2015
A 65 year old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker from Riyadh who is currently in critical condition. There was no history of contact with other case(s).

Information on newly confirmed case from yesterday, 28 Jun 2015 [the information was not available at the time of preparation of yesterday's update]
(http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/CCC/PressReleases/Pages/Statistics-2015-06-28-001.aspx)

A 40 year old Saudi male, non-healthcare worker from Riyadh who was in critical condition at the time of report. There was no history of contact with other case(s)

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This is now the 2nd presumably sporadic case of MERS-CoV infection in individuals in Riyadh. The previously reported cases in Riyadh were reported on 14 Jun 2015, 5 Jun 2015, 18 May 2015, and 4 cases reported on 11 May 2015. All 7 cases had denied a history of contact with other cases, 2 reported contact with camels and ingestion of camel's milk. Hence, of the 9 cases of MERS-CoV infection reported by Riyadh since the beginning of May 2015, 7 would be considered sporadic cases. All but one of the cases gave a history of pre-existing co-morbidities, it would be of interest to know if they sought medical attention for their pre-existing co-morbidities during the 14 days preceding onset of illness.

It is also noteworthy to mention that there have not been reports of newly confirmed cases in Hufoof for the past 4 days -- 24 more days of no newly confirmed cases in Hufoof and transmission will be considered interrupted.

A map showing the location of Riyadh in Saudi Arabia can be found at the source URL. The HealthMap/ProMED map of Saudi Arabia can be found at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3472461,131. - Mod.MPP]

